==English==
===Etymology===
Greek ''geographia'', from ''geos'' [[earth]] + ''graphia'' ([[-graphy]])
===Pronunciation===
/dʒɪˈɒgrəfi/, /<tt>dZI"Qgr@fi</tt>/
===Noun===
'''geography''' (''uncountable'')

<!-- #The graphing or measuring of earth studies, and land. is this an old meaning, or just the literal one?-->
#The study of the physical [[structure]] and inhabitants of the [[Earth]].

